 angular-di: Implement dependency injection in Angular v20+ using inject(), injection tokens, and p (file: r1/angular-di/SKILL.md)\n- angular-directives: Create custom directives in Angular v20+ for DOM manipulation and behavior extension.  (file: r1/angular-directives/SKILL.md)\n- angular-forms: Build signal-based forms in Angular v21+ using the new Signal Forms API. Use for for (file: r1/angular-forms/SKILL.md)\n- angular-http: Implement HTTP data fetching in Angular v20+ using resource(), httpResource(), and Htt (file: r1/angular-http/SKILL.md)\n- angular-new-app: Creates a new Angular app using the Angular CLI. This skill should be used whenever  (file: r1/angular-new-app/SKILL.md)\n- angular-routing: Implement routing in Angular v20+ applications with lazy loading, functional guards, (file: r1/angular-routing/SKILL.md)\n- angular-signals: Implement signal-based reactive state management in Angular v20+. Use for creating r (file: r1/angular-signals/SKILL.md)\n- angular-ssr: Implement server-side rendering and hydration in Angular v20+ using @angular/ssr. Us (file: r1/angular-ssr/SKILL.md)\n- angular-testing: Write unit and integration tests for Angular v20+ applications using Vitest or Jasmi (file: r1/angular-testing/SKILL.md)\n- angular-tooling: Use Angular CLI and development tools effectively in Angular v20+ projects. Use for  (file: r1/angular-tooling/SKILL.md)\n- atlas: macOS-only AppleScript control for the ChatGPT Atlas desktop app. Use only when the  (file: r0/atlas/SKILL.md)\n- browser:control-in-app-browser: Control the in-app Browser for opening, navigating, inspecting visible or interactive  (file: r3/browser/26.715.31925/skills/control-in-app-browser/SKILL.md)\n- chrome:control-chrome: Control the user's Chrome browser for tasks that depend on existing Chrome state: ta (file: r3/chrome/26.715.31925/skills/control-chrome/SKILL.md)\n- codex-security:attack-path-analysis: Use when Codex is already in the attack-path-analysis phase of a security scan or