{"timestamp":"2026-07-19T17:40:37.314Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"The fix’s first execution passed; the stress command then exposed an unrelated fixture limitation: `--repeat-each` reuses the same deterministic tenant ID, so repetitions 2–10 collide on the database primary key. I’m switching to the repository’s supported full-suite run, which gives each collected test its normal isolated fixture and is the result that matters for merge eligibility.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-19T17:40:37.314Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","id":"msg_07acb54591783f13016a5d0c14180c819191c5c67fdbfeb874","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"The fix’s first execution passed; the stress command then exposed an unrelated fixture limitation: `--repeat-each` reuses the same deterministic tenant ID, so repetitions 2–10 collide on the database primary key. I’m switching to the repository’s supported full-suite run, which gives each collected test its normal isolated fixture and is the result that matters for merge eligibility."}],"phase":"commentary","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f7b3b-61db-7f22-b04f-a7cc62c9b8f9"}}}
