{"timestamp":"2026-07-19T17:52:21.826Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Portless is directionally a very good fit here because it replaces worktree-specific ports with stable named local origins—the exact thing Auth0 needs for allowlisted callbacks. I’m checking its current routing/TLS/CLI behavior and Auth0 constraints before recommending whether to adopt it repo-wide; the docs suite continues running meanwhile.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
