{"timestamp":"2026-07-19T17:52:49.806Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call_output","id":"ctco_019f7b82-608e-7130-bfe5-e33eb3d4762e","call_id":"call_FrJ2Vs6IF4Vc7xVcU4LEPtdi","output":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Script completed\nWall time 0.1 seconds\nOutput:\n"},{"type":"input_text","text":"{\"chunk_id\":\"16f9c8\",\"wall_time_seconds\":0.000004042,\"exit_code\":0,\"original_token_count\":3749,\"output\":\".env.dev.local:2:ISSUER_BASE_URL=https://tumi-dev.eu.auth0.com\\n.env.example:10:ISSUER_BASE_URL=\\ntests/support/fixtures/base-test.ts:55:const databaseUrl = environment.DATABASE_URL;\\nsrc/server/registrations/addon-purchase.postgres.spec.ts:38:const databaseUrl = process.env['DATABASE_URL'];\\nsrc/server/registrations/addon-purchase.postgres.spec.ts:40:  throw new Error('DATABASE_URL is required for PostgreSQL integration tests');\\nsrc/server/registrations/addon-purchase.postgres.spec.ts:109:        BASE_URL: 'https://addon-purchase.example',\\nsrc/server/registrations/addon-purchase.postgres.spec.ts:110:        DATABASE_URL: url,\\ntests/README.md:188:`POSTGRES_INTEGRATION_DATABASE_URL` are present. A loopback URL is accepted\\ntests/README.md:193:POSTGRES_INTEGRATION_DATABASE_URL='postgresql://evorto:integration@localhost:5432/evorto_postgres_integration' \\\\\\ntests/README.md:225:  `BASE_URL` before this mode; host-runtime reuse is deliberately disabled so a\\ntests/README.md:238:- Docker keeps `BASE_URL` browser-facing for Auth0 redirects and sets\\ntests/README.md:242:  outbound links to retain the worktree-local `BASE_URL` port.\\ntests/README.md:243:- Auth0 callback URLs are registered out-of-band. Worktree-local generated\\ntests/README.md:245:  needs a callback URL Auth0 accepts. On this machine, run Docker-backed\\ntests/README.md:464:- `DATABASE_URL`\\ntests/README.md:465:- `BASE_URL`\\ntests/README.md:474:- `ISSUER_BASE_URL`\\ntests/README.md:602:- distinct local app port and `BASE_URL`\\ntests/support/utils/post-registr